"NOT FOUND"|"1. 7. plerosque Belgas esse ortos, &c. The Remi seem to except themselves and the Suessiones. Tacitus is probably right when he says (Germ. 28) that the Belgae claimed a German origin from the wish to separate themselves from the despised1. 10. ea loca, ***that district.' The distinction between the neut loca and the masc. loci is very accurately observed by Homan writers. Loca is used of places, spots, districts on the earth***s surface, or of places in a college or corporation: loci are rhetorical topics or commonplaces."

