"NOT FOUND"|"1. 25. sectionem . . . vendidit, ***Caesar sold the State-lot of that town in a lump.* Sectio is that portion of the booty which the State appropriated, and whicji was generally sold by auction. The bidders in such sales for such sectiones were called sectores. There was other booty got from the town, but that claimed by the State***the sectio eius oppidi***was all sold. The people composing the sectio might have been presented with their liberty."

